description:
Parse and write log notes as nested bullets in journal markdown.

## Files to Modify
- `internal/journal/parser.go` - Parse nested note bullets
- `internal/journal/writer.go` - Write notes as nested bullets

## Changes

### parser.go (lines 131-135)
Update log section parsing to detect 2-space indented bullets:
```go
case SectionLog:
    if strings.HasPrefix(line, "  - ") && len(j.LogEntries) > 0 {
        // Parse as note for last log entry
        noteText := strings.TrimSpace(strings.TrimPrefix(line, "  - "))
        noteID, text := extractNoteID(noteText)
        if noteID == "" {
            noteID = xid.New().String()
        }

        lastIdx := len(j.LogEntries) - 1
        note := LogNote{ID: noteID, Text: text, Position: len(j.LogEntries[lastIdx].Notes)}
        j.LogEntries[lastIdx].Notes = append(j.LogEntries[lastIdx].Notes, note)
    } else if entry := parseLogEntry(trimmed, j.Date, logPos); entry != nil {
        j.LogEntries = append(j.LogEntries, *entry)
        logPos++
    }
```

Add helper at end of file:
```go
func extractNoteID(text string) (id string, remaining string)
```

### writer.go (lines 93-106)
After writing log entry, add:
```go
if len(entry.Notes) > 0 {
    // Sort and write notes
    for _, note := range sortedNotes {
        sb.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("  - [%s] %s\n", note.ID, note.Text))
    }
}
```

